From: As Tsaqib <0xfiqks@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 20 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] profile: download: always gate interactive preview

`profile download -p` only asked for confirmation when the provider supplied
profile metadata. If metadata was absent, lpac continued directly into
prepareDownload and profile installation without user approval.

Keep metadata reporting conditional, but move the y/n gate outside that
condition so EOF, an unavailable prompt, and every answer other than y/Y fail
closed before es10b_prepare_download().
---
 src/applet/profile/download.c | 15 ++++++++-------
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+), 7 deletions(-)

--- a/src/applet/profile/download.c
+++ b/src/applet/profile/download.c
@@ -243,13 +243,14 @@ static int applet_main(int argc, char **
 
         jprint_progress_obj("es8p_meatadata_parse", jmetadata);
 
-        if (interactive_preview) {
-            char c;
-            jprint_progress("preview", "y/n");
-            c = getchar();
-            if (c != 'y' && c != 'Y') {
-                cancelled = 1;
-            }
+    }
+
+    if (interactive_preview) {
+        int answer;
+        jprint_progress("preview", "y/n");
+        answer = getchar();
+        if (answer != 'y' && answer != 'Y') {
+            cancelled = 1;
         }
     }
 
